abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump on Tuesday issued a stark warning to congressional Democrats, saying that if they pursue impeachment against him they will be "declaring war on American democracy."
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump on Tuesday issued a stark warning to congressional Democrats, saying that if they pursue impeachment against him they will be "declaring war on American democracy."
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump on Tuesday issued a stark warning to congressional Democrats, saying that if they pursue impeachment against him they will be "declaring war on American democracy."
headline_main: Trump Labels U.S. House Impeachment Drive 'Partisan Coup'
headline_print_headline: Trump Labels U.S. House Impeachment Drive 'Partisan Coup'

lead_paragraph: ’Twas the eve of impeachment, when all through the HouseNo Republicans wavered, each last one a louse.

abstract: President Trump sent a letter on Tuesday to Speaker Nancy Pelosi expressing his “most powerful protest” against the impeachment process. The House is expected to vote on two articles of impeachment against Mr. Trump on Wednesday.

lead_paragraph: President Trump sent a letter on Tuesday to Speaker Nancy Pelosi expressing his “most powerful protest” against the impeachment process. The House is expected to vote on two articles of impeachment against Mr. Trump on Wednesday.

headline_main: India’s Internet Crackdown, Swine Fever, The Vatican: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: The contrast over U.S. demands to protect Chinese Uighurs and Myanmar’s Rohingya will be an undercurrent in high-level meetings with India this week.
snippet: The contrast over U.S. demands to protect Chinese Uighurs and Myanmar’s Rohingya will be an undercurrent in high-level meetings with India this week.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — China’s detention of one million ethnic Uighur Muslims has been described by Secretary of State Mike Pompeo as Orwellian, a “gross human rights violation” and “one of the worst stains on the world of this century.”

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday he backed Bolivia's interim President Jeanine Anez as she seeks "a peaceful democratic transition," and he denounced ongoing violence in the country.

abstract: The top U.S. diplomat in Ukraine will be leaving his post at the beginning of next year after a term convulsed by the impeachment inquiry into President Donald Trump, two officials said Tuesday.

abstract: A Vietnam veteran with decades of State Department experience, William B. Taylor Jr. sharply objected to what he saw as the Trump administration’s shadow foreign policy in Ukraine.
snippet: A Vietnam veteran with decades of State Department experience, William B. Taylor Jr. sharply objected to what he saw as the Trump administration’s shadow foreign policy in Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — William B. Taylor Jr., the top American diplomat in Ukraine who described for Congress and the public what he saw as President Trump’s efforts to pressure Kyiv to go after political rivals, said on Tuesday that he was stepping down from his post.

headline_main: Before a Historic Impeachment: ‘Right vs. Wrong’

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives on Tuesday approved a $1.4 trillion spending package to avert a partial government shutdown that also would raise the U.S. tobacco purchasing age to 21 and permanently repeal several of the Affordable Care Act's (ACA) taxes.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. House of Representatives on Tuesday approved a $1.4 trillion spending package to avert a partial government shutdown that also would raise the U.S. tobacco purchasing age to 21 and permanently repeal several of the Affordable Care Act's (ACA) taxes.
headline_main: House Approves $1.4 Trillion Spending Deal to Avert Shutdown, Sends to Senate
